# Adding a New DeviceType to the Highlighter

`TerminalHighlighter` in `src/renderer/src/lib/highlighter.ts` is a streaming, line-level highlighter.
Only **complete lines** (followed by `\n`) are processed — partial chunks pass through untouched.

## Steps

1. Add the new vendor to the `DeviceType` union in `src/types/shared.ts`
2. Write a `highlight<Vendor>(line: string): string` function in `highlighter.ts`
3. Add a `case '<vendor>':` entry in the `highlightLine` switch

## Shared Helpers

```ts
col(ansiCode, text)   // wrap text in an ANSI escape sequence
colorIPs(line)        // colorise IP/IPv6/MAC addresses in a line
```

## Example

```ts
function highlightMyVendor(line: string): string {
  line = colorIPs(line)
  if (/^error/i.test(line)) return col(31, line)  // red
  return line
}

// in highlightLine switch:
case 'my-vendor':
  return highlightMyVendor(line)
```
